  "text": "The maximum pause time of 2.1ms, measured for the age-oriented collector, is two orders of magnitude shorter than that of Jikes parallel collector. The length of the age-oriented pause time is dominated by the time it takes to scan the roots of a single thread (occurring in one of the handshakes). This operation also dominates the pause time of the previous on-the-fly collectors [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and thus their pause times are similar (see [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] for specific measurements of pause times for these collectors). Hence, the age-oriented collector achieves a significant throughput improvement over the original reference counting collector and over the generational collectors, while retaining the short pause times.",
